#Text=County Galway
#Text=County Galway ( Irish : Contae na Gaillimhe ) is on the West coast of Ireland , in the province of Connacht .
#Text=It is noted for its fantastic scenery in the Connemara region and along the shores of Galway Bay and out in the Aran Islands .
#Text=It is also home to one of the larger freshwater lakes , Lough Corrib which at one time was famous for salmon fishing .
#Text=The Irish Language held out longer in the West and as a result it has the largest Gaeltacht in the country .
#Text=Cities
#Text=( Gaillimh ) – county capital situated on Galway Bay
#Text=Towns

#Text=Other destinations
#Text=( Iomaidh ) – a tidal island near Claddaghduff
#Text=( Oileáin Árann ) – lie just off the coast of Connemara .
#Text=Understand
#Text=The Irish name for this county , Gaillimh , derives from Gaill , the Gaelic word for outsiders or foreigners .
#Text=It is ironic , then , that this county is now home to the largest gaeltacht , where the language and culture of Ireland still survives .
#Text=The landscape in County Galway is varied .
#Text=The interior is largely flat , while the Connemara , in the northwest is a region of ancient glacier scarred mountains , blanket bog peatlands and rugged coastlines .

#Text=The Aran Islands and the south are rocky and barren places , containing numerous stone age forts , including Dun Aenghus ( one of the best examples of its kind in Europe ) , beautiful in its isolation .
#Text=To top it off , there is also the urban landscape of Galway City , the west coast 's largest city .
#Text=Talk
#Text=Both English and Irish Gaelic are widely spoken in County Galway .
#Text=As with the rest of Ireland , most Irish speakers are found in smaller and more isolated villages , while the cities are dominantly English speaking .
#Text=Get in
#Text=Frequent Citylink buses and IrishRail trains arrive from Dublin into Galway City .
#Text=Local Bus Éireann buses into smaller communities in County Galway also arrive from neighbouring counties .
#Text=By bus
#Text=Bus Éireann is the main public transportation operator between smaller towns .
#Text=Their network radiates outward from Galway City
#Text=By boat
#Text=Aran Island Ferries and Inis Mór Ferries operate ferries to the Aran Islands
#Text=By car hire
#Text=Car hire is available from several agencies in the city and at the airport .
#Text=Avis
#Text=Budget Car Rental Ireland - Locations at both Galway Airport and Eyre Sq in Galway City Center
#Text=Hertz
#Text=Alamo / National
#Text=Dan Dooley
#Text=Enterprise Rent a Car
#Text=Several local car dealers operate car-rentals .
#Text=These include :
#Text=Windsor Motors - located at Ballybrit
#Text=Arch Motors - located at Westside
#Text=Roads outside the larger towns are often narrow and windy .
#Text=Although this encourages you to slow down and appreciate the wonderful ( if a little bleak ) scenery , it does mean that getting around will probably take longer than you think .
#Text=See
#Text=Lynch 's Castle on Shop Street .
#Text=Probably the finest medieval town house in Ireland .
#Text=It is now a branch of the Allied Irish Bank .
#Text=The Church of Ireland
#Text=St. Nicholas ' Collegiate Church
#Text=.
#Text=is the largest medieval church still in everyday use in Ireland .
#Text=It was founded in 1320 and enlarged in the following two centuries .
#Text=It is a particularly pleasant building in the heart of the old city .
#Text=Galway Cathedral .
#Text=Its Roman Catholic counterpart , the Galway Cathedral was consecrated in 1965 and is a far larger , more imposing building constructed from limestone .

#Text=It has an eclectic style , with renaissance dome , pillars and round arches , and a Romanesque portico that dominates the main facade — which is an unusual feature in modern Irish church building .
#Text=It was suggested by a church in the city of Salamanca in Spain .
#Text=National University of Ireland , Galway .

#Text=Not far from the cathedral stands the original quadrangle building of National University of Ireland , Galway which was erected in 1849 the Great Famin ) as one of the three colleges of the Queen 's University of Ireland ( along with Queen 's University Belfast and University College Cork .
#Text=The university holds the UNESCO archive of spoken material for the Celtic languages .
#Text=Hotel Meyrick .
#Text=Another of the city 's limestone buildings is the Hotel Meyrick , originally the Railway Hotel and then the Great Southern Hotel , built by the Great Southern Railway Company in 1845 .
#Text=Sitting at the southern perimeter of Eyre Square , it is the City 's oldest hotel still in operation .
#Text=Spanish Arch .
#Text=The Spanish Arch in the southwest of the city , was built as an extension to the city walls , a part of which can be seen in the Corrbret Court shopping centre .
#Text=The remains of the Menlo castle can also be seen , outside the city .
#Text=Taibhdhearc na Gaillimhe .
#Text=Galway has a permanent Irish language theatre located in the city centre , Taibhdhearc na Gaillimhe , which has produced some of Ireland 's most celebrated actors .
#Text=The Druid Theatre Company has won international acclaim for its cutting edge production and direction
#Text=Galway City Museum .
#Text=The Galway City Museum features two parts , " Fragments of a City " and " On Reflection . "

#Text=" Fragments of a City" 's collection is mainly about the heritage of Galway , while " On Reflection " is a collection of the most important Irish artists from the second half of the 20th century .
#Text=This museum was designed to allow tourists and local visitors to really get to understand and know the city of Galway .
#Text=Athenry Castle 15 km east of Galway is a restored 13th C Norman keep , open daily April-Oct .
#Text=Aughnanure Castle is a well-restored Gaelic tower house .
#Text=It 's by the shores of Lough Corrib , 20 km northwest of the city towards Oughterard .
#Text=It 's open daily March-Oct , M - Sa Nov.
#Text=Coole Park is a nature reserve in Gort , south of Galway towards the border with County Clare .
#Text=Open daily April-Sept .
#Text=Portumna Castle is a Jacobean mansion at the head of Loch Derg .
#Text=Open daily March-Oct .
#Text=Ionad Cultúrtha
#Text=an Phiarsaigh
#Text=is a cultural centre for the Connemara Gaeltacht .
#Text=It 's at Rosmuc , open daily .
